8:
Mm... He looked kind of shifty...
Let's tail him!
13:
Alk! Does privacy mean nothing to 
you?
16:
*sniff* Ahh... Smells like a spicy love 
affair!
21: Who taught you to speak like that?
25: A manor... It looks old... or unkempt.
28:
Mm... Guess he's NOT chasing after 
the love of his life.
32:
It's too early for certainty...
Look! He's moved!
37:
("Alk," he said. "Respect his privacy," 
he said.)
45:
Don't be absurd. She was merely 
frightened by his appearance.
51:
He is a kind and honorable man... 
She does not know how fortunate 
she is.
55:
Wait. You still think we're witnessing 
some kind of romance?
59:
What'd he slip under the door? 
A letter?
63: One professing his love, no doubt.
70:
*sigh* Had the door slammed in 
my face... again.
81: D'ah! What are you two doing here?!
85:
Tomorrow will bring new hope. But 
tonight, we shall drink away your 
sorrows!
95:
Wait. You've been donating money to 
this orphanage... every month?!
98: Yeah, but it's really not much...
102:
It is a noble deed. Why conduct it in 
secrecy?
107:
So... It, uh... took me a long time to 
screw up enough courage to 
introduce myself.
110:
Long enough for the kids to start 
making up stories about me... and 
calling me Daddy-Long-Legs.
117:
Yeah... Bet it wouldn't be as popular 
if Daddy-Long-Legs was a big, tough-
looking guy covered in scars... I just 
don't want to disappoint the kids.
119:
And I get I'm probably making too big 
a deal out of this. But you know me... 
A coward to the core.
126:
Yeah. You're always on the front lines, 
defending us.
129:
I defend because I can't attack. 
And I wouldn't even be able to defend 
if I weren't so big...
132:
To tell the truth, I didn't even really 
want to be an adventurer. 
But everyone around me kept saying 
I had the build for it, so... I just let them 
talk me into it.
136:
Size does not make you immune to 
pain. It does not guard you from the 
bite of steel or the sting of arrows.
138:
No matter how your knees may shake 
or your hands may tremble, you have 
always stood your ground.
140:
The brave are not those who feel no 
fear. The brave are those who protect 
their comrades, despite that fear... 
Walter. Your scars are proof of your 
courage.
151:
I can't believe... *sniff* I can't believe 
a CHAMPION said that to me!
159:
Okay... I'll do it! I'll march up to those 
kids and tell them sorry I'm not 
Daddy-Long-Legs!
162:
That's not something you need 
apologize for...
164:
Walter... You may frighten the children 
on your first meeting. But do not be 
disheartened.
167:
Mm... More like, your first three 
meetings.
174:
But they'll love you after that! 
Probably.
178: Phew... Okay... I can do this!
